Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine pink-buff. Rectangular stamp with pilos and star symbols.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '285'. Name Diophantos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0261.01, with symbols preserved.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (135)
